Anti-aliased polyphase k=2 (L=1500, pk_k2_filt). 31-tap FIR Hamming low-pass at Nyquist=250 Hz, applied with filtfilt for zero phase, BEFORE taking each phase. RF=311 sub-samples = 622 raw-ms. Default channels (64/128/256), ~436k params. CONTROL: at k=2 there is little EEG content above 250 Hz, so the unfiltered apr25 result (+0.345) and this filtered run should be ~equal. Significant divergence would be a red flag.